SIMPLE: scute
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Scute
<hw>Scute</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>scutum</ets> a
shield, a buckler. See <er>Scudo</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A small
shield.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Skelton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>An old French gold coin of the value of 3s. 4d.
sterling, or about 80 cents.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A bony scale of a reptile or
fish; a large horny scale on the leg of a bird, or on the belly of a
snake.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Scutella</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
